When you browse our website, information on your browsing may be stored in “cookies” files installed on your computer, tablet or smartphone. Cookies are used for: 1. Display of the information strip on the presence of cookies and the possibilities available to you for managing cookies on our site is managed by a cookie. The purpose of this cookie is to enable display of this information strip on your first visit to the site. 2. Cookies enable us to know the number of visits to the website, the number of pages looked at, the browser used, etc. This information enables us to improve the site (user-friendliness, etc.). This data is not personalized. 3. We collect data at various times via the tags and cookies placed on different pages of the site to enable advertisers to create more targeted advertisements for the user. We do not collect personal data and consequently can never link the data we collect to a physical or legal person. Aggregated Personal Information: We partner with third parties that collect information across various channels, including offline and online, for purposes of delivering more relevant advertising and content to you. Our partner may place or recognise a cookie on your computer or device and we may share personal information with them if you have submitted such information to us, such as your email address. Our partners may link the personal information we share with them to the cookie stored on your browser or device, and they may collect information such as your IP address, browser or operating system type and version, and demographic or inferred-interest information. Our partners use this information to recognise you across different channels and platforms over time for advertising, analytics, attribution, and reporting purposes. For example, our partners may deliver and/or enable downstream delivery of an ad to you in your web browser based on a purchase you made in a physical retail store, or they may send a personalised marketing email to you based on the fact that you visited a particular website. To learn more about interests-based advertising in general and to opt-out, please visit https://www.youronlinechoices.com You can also refuse cookies via the settings of your browser as follow: For Internet Explorer, click here For Mozilla Firefox, click here For Google Chrome, click here For Safari, click here To know more about Liveramp advertising cookies and opting out: :  http://liveramp.uk/cookies-101/ How do you delete cookies? You can deactivate cookies. Your browser can also be set to alert you of the cookies that are placed on your computer and ask you if you wish to accept them or otherwise. You can accept or refuse cookies on a case by case basis or you can automatically refuse them once and for all. Please remember that this setting is likely to alter your conditions of access to our services that require use of cookies. Complaints If you consider that we do not comply with this privacy policy, you can contact us at the same address as given above.